name: GYM
about: Nature builds things that are antifragile. In the case of evolution, nature uses disorder to grow stronger. Occasional starvation or going to the gym also makes you stronger, because you subject your body to stressors and gain from them.

name: Read Time
about: I have a passion for teaching kids to become readers, to become comfortable with a book, not daunted. Books shouldn’t be daunting, they should be funny, exciting and wonderful; and learning to be a reader gives a terrific advantage.

name: Playing
about: Playing games is the best time of life, and the more games you get, the better it is. Playing games can contribute to making you happy, perhaps even without therapy.

name: Cycling
about: Riding a bike is everything to a cyclist. The friendship and camaraderie you have with other cyclists… to a cyclist, it was the be-all and end-all of your life.

name: Family
about: Being a family means you are a part of something very wonderful. It means you will love and be loved for the rest of your life.

name: Friends
about: Friendship is the hardest thing in the world to explain. It’s not something you learn in school. But if you haven’t learned the meaning of friendship, you really haven’t learned anything.
